Show container id in list without --sync

The CONTAINER ID column was only populated when --sync queried the
backend; plain "rumpel list" always showed it blank. The backend name
(docker/podman container name, kubernetes pod name) is a pure function
of the repo path and pod name, both of which the daemon already
persists, so derive it at list time instead of querying the backend.
This keeps the column correct across daemon restarts, needs no DB
schema change, and replaces the docker hash id with the container
name, which docker accepts wherever it accepts ids. The value is no
longer truncated to 12 characters since the hash prefix convention no
longer applies and the shared "rumpel-<repo>" prefix would make
truncated names indistinguishable.
